sentences: Agnes Tyrrell (20 September 1846 – 18 April 1883) was a composer and pianist of English and Czech descent.
Tyrrell was one of the few women to compose a symphony before 1900.

In 2018, her Overture in C Minor received a world premiere performance by the Orchester L'anima giusta conducted by Jessica Horsley at the Frauenkomponiert Festival in Bern and recorded by Swiss Radio.
